{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"577dbc45-1527-47ae-9b47-0af2180ea063","content":"\n\nTo switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Remove this line entirely, or set to false -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n   MSTest.Sdk 3.8+ defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `UseVSTest` is absent/false.\n\n2. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   or directly via the built executable (Microsoft.Testing.Platform produces a self-contained test host).\n\n**Key behavioral differences to watch for:**\n\n- **CLI output** format changes (more structured, less verbose by default).\n- **`--filter`** syntax is the same, but some advanced VSTest `.runsettings` options may need adjustment.\n- **Extensions** like code coverage or loggers now use the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.*` NuGet packages instead of VSTest adapters.\n- If you use a **`.runsettings`** file, most settings carry over, but verify any custom VSTest-specific nodes.\n\nThat's it — with MSTest.Sdk, the migration is essentially flipping that one property.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f71f080f-1551-4b9b-aed0-cc3de9081016","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project that uses MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing migration, not a code change request in a specific repository.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":390},"id":"acaed629-7b75-41e8-b53c-9397b7644bab","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:46:15.732Z","parentId":"c66ab889-562a-43bc-bedc-0c13cd5179ff"}
